This paper deals with the problem of multi-document summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The use of variational auto-encoders (VAEs) and deep learning (DL) techniques also suggests a connection to the subfield of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). The focus on reader comments and the creation of a new dataset for evaluation may also indicate a connection to the subfield of human-computer interaction (HCI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
